    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_gt.00069_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Brooklyn</name> 
                    <date when="1891-10-12">Oct 12<hi rend="underline">th</hi>/91.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>
                    Dear Friend <choice><sic>Water</sic><corr>Walter</corr></choice>,
                </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                I was reading an article in a Magazine the other day; &amp; came across an interesting account of a birthday 
                meeting of your friends,<ptr target="loc.04326_n3"/> &amp; at this late day would like to add my greeting to you, as an old friend.
            </p>
            <p>
               May the good "Lord" give you continued life and loving friends to cheer you on the journey. 
            </p>
            <p>
                Please remember me to Jeff.<ptr target="n4995"/> Can you give me his address.
            </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>
                    From your friend,
                </salute>
                <signed rend="right">Sam'l G. Stanley</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>323 Macon St</addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
            <note type="editorial" place="bottom" resp="#ww">Sam'l G Stanley Brooklyn</note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_gt.00070_large.jpg" type="verso"/> 
             <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#unk">S.G. Stanley</note>
        </body>
